A Very Nice Experience at the Al Quadra Cycling Track and Trek Store
Mar 2023
The Al Quadra Cycling Track is a popular destination for cycling enthusiasts, and it's always good to have a reliable bike shop nearby. It's clear that the staff at the Trek store are knowledgeable and skilled bike mechanics who take pride in their work. If you needed any repairs or adjustments to your bike, it's great to know that they were able to help you out.
Another great thing to note about the Trek store at Al Quadra is that they offer bike rentals. This is a convenient option for anyone who doesn't have their own bike or is visiting from out of town. With a variety of bikes available for rent, including road bikes and mountain bikes, there is something for everyone. And with the helpful staff on hand, they can assist in finding the right bike for your needs and ensure that it's properly fitted for your comfort and safety. So, whether you're a local looking to explore the Al Quadra Cycling Track or a visitor wanting to experience the beautiful desert scenery on two wheels, renting a bike from the Trek store can be a great option.
Written March 31, 2023

50 km Dubai Desert Challenge in aid of The Christie Cancer Charity
Mar 2022 • Couples
Whilst in dubai on holiday , I had planned a 50 km fundraising ride through the desert.

Bikes - The Trek Cycle Centre hires bikes relatively cheaply and supplies helmets , we hire 2 road bikes for 4 hours and it worked out at £50.

Getting there - We got a taxi from our hotel on the Palm about 45 minutes BUT beware we booked the bikes 2pm-6pm and struggled to get a taxi back . The guys at the Trek shop organised for someone to get us back to the hotel.

The track has shelters , to get some rest bite from the sun , but no toilets or water one you leave the start.

The track is signpost well with markers to tell you how far you have gone.

Its a great experience but boy is it hot , we choose the wrong time but lots of riders were turning up as the sun began to set.

I cannot praise the guys at the Trek shop enough they were lovely.
Written March 13, 2022

Warsaw, Poland17 contributions
Al Qudra - going from Dubai and back using Car sharing
Feb 2022
Excellent cycling paths! During my resent visit at Dubai I also. visited Al Qudra cycling path and I can highly recommend this place!

My challange was how to get there and back from Dubai. Here was my approach:

1. How the get there?
I sign up at uDrive - car sharing - there is one more even more popular car sharing but I wanted to make it simple and uDrive was first I enrolled. The other one is Ekar - both have an mobile app to manage entire rental.

2. Signing up at uDrive was not a smooth process but after several trial of uploading photos of documents, selfie with my documents, visa stamp from pasport etc my application was accepted

3. In Feb - no need to be there so early as the temperature and sun are manageable so I start looking for my car ca 8:30 with the aim to start my ride at 10:00.

4. I found a car near by me and rent it - opening the car was a bit tricky as the GPS location and the GPS of the car was not 100% matched even I was standing next to the car and holding doors waiting to be opened. Buildings are so high which can distruct GPS signal. Just be patient.. or find another car near to you.

5. Once doors opened, it took me ca 40mins point to point to get to Al Qudra

6. I rented one of the bike at Bike Trek shop/rental - they don't have bike shoos to rent

7. Left or right?
The main cycling path is a circle so you need to decide which way to go - and here is a little detail only locals or somebody who used the path already knows - observe other bikers where they go left or right - I felt the difference ca 20km - the dessert wind direction make the difference:-) I wish I new it before my start - even at the rental space they don't rather tell you this. Instead they say you can go left or right - no difference but there is a difference as the wind usually appear there

8. When I return I was charged by uDrive 142 AED - all inclusive (car, petrol, insurance) - whole day rate.

9. Car sharing - there is a term called Business Zone - the zone where uDrive operate - it's not so clear at the beginning if I can go with the car outside the zone or not - Al Qudra is outside the zone - don't worry - I found finally in the Q&A that car can be used in any place in UAE but cannot be left outside the Business Zone - left mean finishing the rental. Of course then we can go to place like Al Qudra and after we cycling we can get back to Business Zone and finish rental leaving the car on one of the parking space

Wish to come back - amazing place to be!
Written February 5, 2022
